    {
      "id": "18157763",
      "type": "tasks",
      "attributes": {
        "title": "STR_050 Federal Budget - Media Analysis",
        "description": "<div>Brief Writer: Tasha<br>Priority: High<br>Review Date: 2026-06-04<br><br>Why are we here (the background):<br>Media Analysis report on Federal Budget: <a href=\"https://www.streem.com.au/hubfs/Budget%20AU%202026-2027/Streem%20Australian%20Federal%20Budget%202026-27%20Media%20Analysis%20Report.pdf\">https://www.streem.com.au/hubfs/Budget%20AU%202026-2027/Streem%20Australian%20Federal%20Budget%202026-27%20Media%20Analysis%20Report.pdf</a><br><br>translating dense analyst piece into linkedin social content <br><br>What do we need to create:<br>Specs like the listed examples in references please!<br><br>Footer or header small to show theme:<br>Federal Budget 2026–27 Media Analysis | Streem<br><br><br>Title slide: <br><br>Headline: We analysed the media coverage in the aftermath of the Budget. Here’s what we found.<br><br>Data vis:<br>A large swing-style gauge or before/after speedometer showing NSS moving from +16% pre-Budget to -28% post-Budget.<br>Pre-Budget NSS: +16%<br>Post-Budget NSS: -28%<br><br>[tiny data blurb \"Streem Data: Traditional media sentiment analysis. 9–17 May 2026]<br><br>Slide 2:<br><br>Headline:<br>Sentiment shifted sharply after Budget Day.<br><br>Data vis:<br>Use two vertical proportional  stacked sentiment bars comparing pre-Budget and post-Budget coverage. (page 5 sentiment charts is where data is from)<br><br>Pre-Budget:<br>Positive: 13%<br>Trending positive: 22%<br>Neutral: 46%<br>Trending negative: 13%<br>Negative: 6%<br><br>Post-Budget:<br>Positive: 3%<br>Trending positive: 15%<br>Neutral: 36%<br>Trending negative: 28%<br>Negative: 18%<br><br>supporting text: The drop was driven by a sharp rise in negative and trending negative coverage, which grew from 19% before Budget Day to 46% after.<br><br>arrow to l to next slide with \"So, what drove the drop?\"<br><br>Small NSS explainer at the bottom, <br><br>human-rated sentiment across tier one publications, Net Sentiment Score = Percentage of positive mentions minus percentage of negative mentions<br><br>[tiny data blurb \"Streem Data: Traditional media sentiment analysis. 9–17 May 2026]<br><br><br>Slide 3:<br>Headline:<br>Tax reform was the pressure point in the media narrative.<br><br>Data vis:<br>Simplified sentiment-by-theme chart from the report (page 6 top chart)<br><br>Focus themes:<br>Cost of Living & Tax Reforms<br>Housing Policies<br>Productivity & Investment<br>Social Services, Welfare & NDIS<br>Energy & Oil Policies<br><br>Make Cost of Living & Tax Reforms visually dominant, with negative and trending negative sentiment clearly highlighted. Show Housing Policies and Productivity & Investment as more positive by comparison.<br><br>Key callouts:<br>Cost of Living & Tax Reforms had the highest negative coverage volume.<br>Housing Policies and Productivity & Investment had the most positive coverage.<br><br>Slide 4:<br>Headline:<br>The criticism centred on impact, fairness and trust.<br><br>Data vis:<br>Create three annotated cards connected to the negative sentiment around Cost of Living & Tax Reforms.<br><br>Three small tiles showing the key themes behind negative tax reform coverage: CGT and negative gearing, cost of living and rent pressure, and election promise criticism.<br><br>card 1:<br>CGT and negative gearing<br><br>card 2:<br>Cost of living and rent pressure<br><br>card 3:<br>Election promise criticism<br><br>Supporting copy:<br>Coverage of capital gains tax and negative gearing drew criticism around housing supply, rent impacts, younger Australians’ ability to build wealth, and concerns from business owners and financial commentators.<br><br>Positive-leaning coverage framed the reforms as a move to rebalance the system and support first-home buyers.<br><br>Slide 5:<br><br>Headline:<br>Social discussion centred on the same pressure points, but with an increased focus on housing.<br><br>Data vis:<br>Ranked horizontal bar chart showing leading social media discussion topics.<br>Use these exact figures:<br>Housing: 1,546 posts<br>Capital Gains Tax: 1,085 posts<br>Cost of Living: 879 posts<br>Negative Gearing: 821 posts<br>Migration: 759 posts<br>Infrastructure: 316 posts<br>NDIS: 315 posts<br>Discretionary Trusts Tax: 218 posts<br>Fuel Security: 213 posts<br>Productivity: 204 posts<br><br>could be cool to visually group Capital Gains Tax, Cost of Living and Negative Gearing to show the concentration of attention around tax and household financial pressure.<br><br>Supporting copy:<br><br>Traditional media sentiment turned most sharply around cost of living and tax reform. On social, housing generated the highest discussion volume, followed by capital gains tax, cost of living and negative gearing.<br><br>Final CTA slide to download the full media analysis report 'Want to get granular? Read our full Media Analysis Report'<br><br>Design Direction:<br>We need to be careful around text sizing and thickness so it's legible on mobile, im seeing a lot of posts on LinkedIn that are hard to read.<br><br>References:<br>same specs as these, also cool looking design!<br><br><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brandwatch_social-signals-and-search-activity-7455224791684497408-yOOP?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk\">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brandwatch_social-signals-and-search-activity-7455224791684497408-yOOP?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk</a><br><br><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/gotracksuit_50-of-ads-are-less-engaging-than-activity-7452838735324430338-lXSp?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk\">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/gotracksuit_50-of-ads-are-less-engaging-than-activity-7452838735324430338-lXSp?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk</a><br><br><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/absstats_72-of-australian-businesses-have-been-impacted-activity-7465562496679194624-BlUU?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk\">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/absstats_72-of-australian-businesses-have-been-impacted-activity-7465562496679194624-BlUU?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAACxrPDIBpnqW51peqY39l-0umJ8FDjAUCmk</a><br><br>Other Relevant Info: </div>",
